article.headline: Wofford 75, Texas-Pan American 70
article.story: AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. -- Noah Dahlman scored 21 points as Wofford defeated Texas-Pan American 75-70 in the opening round of the Reggie Minton Air Force Classic tournament on Saturday. Wofford (1-2) led by as many as 16 points in the second half. Texas-Pan American (1-3) trailed 73-68 with 16 seconds to go after Jason Jensen sank a 3-pointer. Junior Salters was fouled and made both free throws to give Wofford a 75-68 lead. The Broncos trailed 75-70 after a layup by Luis Valera with 5 seconds left, but they never got the ball back. Nathan Hawkins led Texas-Pan American in scoring with 22 points.
